@everyone Debugged the Zeus Z-comp issue yesterday. We believe the scan-pass stitching transforms are introducing an artificial bow in the middle of the scan, which is resulting in high Z-comps.
Because the height difference between the front workbench and the pallets exceeds the scanner’s Z range, we’re unable to calibrate the scan-pass stitching transforms using fiducials on the workbench.
The best path forward is to make a calibration plate to tune the transforms. We’re aiming to have it fabricated by the end of this week and to complete calibration early next week.